as garantias ou condições ou a limitação ou exclusão de responsabilidade por perdas e danos. Consequentemente, apenas as limitações que forem permitidas por lei na sua jurisdição se aplicarão a você. Nos casos em que exclusão de responsabilidade não se mostrar possível, mas a limitação de responsabilidade for legalmente aplicável, a responsabilidade total da INC estará limitada a R$ 1.000,00 (um mil Reais). &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><b><br>RESCISÃO E DESCONTINUAÇÃO</b>&nbsp;&nbsp; Não obstante as CGU, a INC reserva-se o direito de, sem aviso-prévio e de acordo com seus únicos e exclusivos critérios, bloquear o seu uso e acesso ao MatchSpot. A INC, ainda, reserva-se no direito de, sem aviso-prévio e de acordo com seus únicos e exclusivos critérios, descontinuar o MatchSpot, parcial ou integralmente.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><b><br>VALIDADE E VIGÊNCIA DAS CLÁUSULAS</b>&nbsp;&nbsp; Qualquer renúncia ou alteração dos dispositivos das CGU só terá efeito caso apresentada por escrito e assinada pelo representante legal da INC. Se uma cláusula das CGU for anulada ou considerada inaplicável, as demais cláusulas, sempre que possível, permanecerão válidas e vigentes. Os direitos não concedidos expressamente restam reservados à INC. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><b><br>ALTERAÇÕES NAS CGU</b>&nbsp;&nbsp; A INC reserva-se no direito de alterar as CGU, bem como qualquer outra política do MatchSpot, a qualquer momento e ao seu exclusivo critério. As alterações entrarão em vigor no momento da respectiva publicação no MatchSpot. O uso do MatchSpot depois da publicação constituirá aceitação de eventuais alterações das CGU. Dessa forma, aconselhamos os usuários a relerem as CGU sempre que acessarem o MatchSpot. Se você não concordar com os termos alterados das CGU, você deve descontinuar o uso do MatchSpot. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><b><br>LEI E FORO APLICÁVEIS</b>&nbsp;&nbsp; Qualquer litígio relacionado ao uso do MatchSpot, aos serviços ofertados através do MatchSpot ou ao respectivo conteúdo deverá ser submetido ao Foro da Comarca de São Paulo, Estado de São Paulo, Brasil, que prevalecerá sobre qualquer outro, por mais privilegiado que seja, e será julgado conforme as leis da República Federativa do Brasil. &nbsp;<br><b><br>PERGUNTAS E ESCLARECIMENTOS</b>&nbsp;&nbsp; Perguntas e comentários sobre o MatchSpot ou sobre as CGU poderão ser dirigidos à INC pelo suporte@matchspot.com.br.&nbsp;<br>';
$enTerms = 'GENERAL CONDITIONS OF USE Last updated: November 6, 2017 PLEASE READ CAREFULLY: BY ACCESSING, USING AND / OR REGISTERING ANY SITES, PROGRAMS, APPLICATIONS OR SERVICES OF&nbsp;INC INOVAÇÕES E TECNOLOGIA LTDA., PRIVATE LAW LEGAL PERSON WITH HEADQUARTERS IN AV. SANTOS DUMONT Nº. 2626, SALA 501, ALDEOTA, CEP 60.150-161, FORTALEZA - CE, ENROLLED IN CNPJ / MF SOB O Nº. 22.890.540 / 0001-20 (\"INC\"), YOU AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS SET FORTH HEREIN, AND WITH THE OTHER POLICIES AND / OR RULES IN THIS INSTRUMENT REFERRED TO. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO ALL OF THESE CONDITIONS, DO NOT USE THE INC. WEBSITES, APPLICATIONS OR SERVICES. These General Conditions of Use (\"CGU\") regulate in particular the use of the site, application hotspots, networks, platform, applications and / or programs, hereinafter referred to as \"MatchSpot\", owned and / or made available by INC. For purposes of the CGU, \"User\" is any and all individuals or legal entities that access and use MatchSpot. When using MatchSpot, you claim to be over 18 years of age or, if a minor, be accompanied by legal representative and be legally qualified to accept the CGU. If you are using MatchSpot on behalf of an entity and / or legal entity, you warrant that you are authorized to accept the CGU on behalf of the respective entity and / or legal entity, as well as ensuring that such entity and / or legal entity agrees to indemnify INC for any violation of the CGU. INC is committed to ensuring your privacy. We recommend checking the \"PRIVACY POLICY\" chapter below for detailed information on how MatchSpot collects, uses and discloses User information. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>MATCHSPOT OPERATION AND UTILIZATION MatchSpot aims to provide, manage and monitor hotspots, which are basically open Wi-Fi networks made available in different establishments for the use and access of their respective customers, as well as serving as a media option for advertisers. In order to use the wifi network in a certain establishment, the User must access the MatchSpot and make their registration, which will allow their access in the wifi network available. INC. May enter into partnerships with legal entities and / or individuals to, among other things, obtain information on location, network operation, promote commercials on MatchSpot, as well as to promote commercial benefits to Users (eg discounts, business advantages, awards etc.). The User authorizes INC to display any advertising in MatchSpot and is aware that any compensation arising from this advertising will be exclusively incumbent upon INC, which is not responsible for the content displayed as advertising, whose responsibility will be solely and exclusively for the advertisers. INC warrants to the User, provided that the CGU is respected, the right to use MatchSpot. However, it is expressly prohibited: (a) to reproduce or retransmit MatchSpot, in whole or in part; (b) use a data mining device and / or similar to collect and / or extract MatchSpot data; (c) manipulate or display the MatchSpot and / or its content using any associated browsing technology or framework; and (d) reverse engineer MatchSpot. In case of violation of the User\'s CGU, INC may, without the need for any notice or prior notice, interrupt the User\'s access to the MatchSpot.&nbsp;<br><br>MATCHSPOT RIGHTS The MatchSpot, as well as all content found on it, including but not limited to text, graphics, data, images, videos, sounds, illustrations, computer programs, source code, trademarks, slogans, domain names, databases, business names, logos, icons, trade dress, as well as the selection and organization of such elements, belong exclusively to the INC and may not be copied, imitated or used in whole or in part. in part, without the prior written permission of the legal representative of INC. The use of meta-tags or any other type of \"hidden code\" containing the expression \"INC\", \"MatchSpot\" or any other expressions similar or similar to trademarks, logos, slogans, domain names and MatchSpot, without the prior written permission of the legal representative of INC, except in cases expressly authorized in these Terms and Conditions.&nbsp;<br><br>PRIVACY POLICY Collection and Use of Information When you access, register and / or otherwise use MatchSpot, the following information and personal data may be requested and collected at the time of registration of a new User, for example: full name of the User ; User qualification (RG and CPF); email; password; telephone; location of the User; address of the User; access history and MatchSpot activities; history of purchases made in MatchSpot; access history and activities on websites for which the User was directed from the link available in MatchSpot; &nbsp; &nbsp;INC uses the information collected for the following purposes: to facilitate the identification and access of the User to MatchSpot; provide the required interactivity to MatchSpot; conduct research and marketing relationship with Users; operate and perfect MatchSpot; assist in the creation or development of new products or services; display customized content in accordance with the interests of Users; prepare statistics in general, including for third parties; provide customer service services; and, • sending information to regulatory agencies and competent authorities; and, sending information to the associated partners, controlling companies, subsidiaries and / or subsidiaries of INC. By accessing or using MatchSpot, you consent to the collection, processing and storage of your personal information and data, subject to the limits of these Terms and Conditions. Information collected by MatchSpot may be stored and processed in any country in which INC or its affiliates, subsidiaries, partners or agents maintain offices, and by using MatchSpot you consent to the transfer of such information outside of your country. MatchSpot may also contain third-party tools and technologies that may collect user information directly, including location information. INC is not responsible for the use that these third parties make or may make of the information of the Users that are collected, stored or processed by them. &nbsp; Information Sharing INC preserves the users\' privacy and undertakes not to share personal information and data with companies, organizations and other individuals, unless (a) if the User is authorized, expressly - eg through the acceptance of a document made available by INC , or (b) in one of the following circumstances: &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>● for external processing: INC may disclose your personal information and data to trusted companies, organizations or individuals with the intent to process and organize them, by providing confidentiality and security instructions to be provided by INC; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>● for the use of the establishments: the User, upon accessing and / or using MatchSpot, is aware that their data will be provided and shared with the establishments through which the User has connected to the MatchSpot network, and Users declare and acknowledge that INC has no direct and / or indirect management and / or responsibility regarding the destination and / or use, treatment and storage that the establishments in question exempt from the Users\' data. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>● when you share your personal information or data in open areas of MatchSpot or with other users or third parties: the User is aware that the information shared with other users and / or any other third parties as a result of using MatchSpot may be viewed / used by INC and by third parties that directly or indirectly use MatchSpot. In this way, the User knows and acknowledges that such information may be accessed by any third party, as well as being fully and exclusively responsible for any risks originating or arising from access of third parties to such information and data; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>● to provide services to INC: INC may share your personal information and data with companies, organizations or individuals that provide services on your behalf. For example, it may hire other companies to store data, host sites, fulfill orders, assist in direct marketing, conduct audits, etc. These companies will receive permission to obtain only the information and data necessary to provide the service properly and may be required to maintain the confidentiality of this data and information. Whenever possible and compatible with the functionality of MatchSpot, the information will be provided in a way that preserves the anonymity of the Users; &nbsp;<br><br>● for legal reasons: INC may disclose or share your information if you have a good faith belief that access, use, preservation or disclosure of information is reasonably necessary to (a) comply with any applicable law, regulation, court order or governmental request ; (b) comply with the UGC or investigate possible violations; (c) detect or prevent fraud and resolve technical or security issues; (d) ensure MatchSpot security; (e) safeguard rights and prevent liabilities of the INC, and; (f) avoid damages to the property or the security of the INC or the Users;&nbsp;<br><br>● INC restructuring: as a result of any corporate restructuring, change of control and / or transfer of assets, INC may share or even transfer the users\' personal information and data to the individuals or legal entities involved; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>● others: INC may use User information and personal data to send newsletters as well as other promotional and marketing materials. Furthermore, INC may make User\'s information available to third parties that provide products and / or services that may be of interest to Users. As long as the terms of these Terms and Conditions are observed and respected, you agree to access and use MatchSpot, the sharing of any information and personal data collected, as well as to receive messages (eg usage guidelines, e-mail marketing, .) in the email provided for registration.&nbsp;<br><br>WE WILL REQUEST YOUR AUTHORIZATION BEFORE USING YOUR INFORMATION FOR ANY PURPOSE OTHER THAN THOSE UNDERSTOOD IN THESE CGU. &nbsp; Use of Cookies and Other Technologies MatchSpot may use cookies or other technologies to help customize your experience. Cookies are small text files stored in your computer\'s memory. A cookie contains information that can be read later by a server located in the domain that issued it. The information that cookies collect includes the date and time of your visit, browsing history, and so on. Cookies and similar technologies bring several benefits, since they allow you to identify old users when they return to MatchSpot, allowing them to target personalized content. Such technologies also save time, making it unnecessary to enter the same information several times. INC may also use or require Users to use plug-ins and / or similar technologies to ensure greater security for transactions made by MatchSpot. Such technologies may scan the terminal or device of the User, capturing and processing information to ensure the security of the transaction and / or prevent fraud. &nbsp; Security of your Personal Information The security of your information and personal data is very important to us. We follow industry safety standards to help protect the information and personal data collected. However, there is no method of electronic storage that is completely secure.&nbsp;<br><br>THEREFORE, ALTHOUGH WE STRIVE TO PROTECT INFORMATION AND DATA COLLECTED, WE CAN NOT GUARANTEE ABSOLUTE SECURITY. Considering this, INC undertakes to adopt the legally required security standards to protect the personal data collected from Users in MatchSpot, as well as to maintain detailed inventory of the access history of all its employees to its database. Restricting access to the database that you store or manage. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>RIGHTS CLAIMS If you believe that MatchSpot or any content contained therein violates the rights of your property or under your control, you may communicate to INC through support@matchspot.com, but INC reserves the right to remove or maintain such content, in accordance with the rules and guidelines of Law 12.965 / 2014. Additionally, you are aware that INC may not be liable for any damages arising from content generated or published by third parties, except in the cases expressly provided for in Law 12.965 / 2014. &nbsp; LINKS You may not frame trademarks, logos, slogans, domain names, corporate names or other information or technologies belonging to INC without the express written consent of the INC legal representative. INC. Does not recommend and is not responsible, directly or indirectly, for the quality, content, nature or reliability of third party sites, products or services accessed through links available through MatchSpot, as well as third party sites, products or services that contain links to MatchSpot. These sites are not under the control of INC and are not responsible for their contents. When you leave MatchSpot or stop using MatchSpot features, the CGU will no longer be applicable. We suggest checking the terms and policies of any site to which you are directed. You agree not to hold INC for any loss, damage or other problems of any kind arising from the use of sites that contain links to MatchSpot, or whose links are available on MatchSpot, and you are aware that any such dealings with such sites does not involve, binds and / or binds INC. &nbsp; INDEMNIFICATION You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless INC, its employees, agents, employees, subcontractors and independent vendors from any and all claims, damages, costs, liabilities, liabilities and / or expenses (including, but not limited to, attorney\'s fees) originating or relating to any content you post, store and / or transmit on or through MatchSpot, your conduct, your use or inability to use MatchSpot, your violation or alleged violation of the MatchSpot\'s GCU and other MatchSpot policies, your unauthorized use of the contents of INC or your violation of any rights of third parties. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>DISCLAIMER OF LIABILITY MatchSpot may not function properly due to network problems and / or due to connection problems of any of the parties involved, situations that are outside the control of the INC and, therefore, will not be the responsibility of the INC. The User is further aware that MatchSpot may not be compatible with other programs installed on Users \'machines or devices or present faults, as yet unknown to the INC, which may obstruct Users\' access, generate incorrect information and / or not store properly the data derived from the activities of the Users. MatchSpot may allow Users to share information and / or content with other Users. The INC does not guarantee and / or assumes no responsibility for any content posted by User, and the User is the sole and exclusive responsible for their posts, and shall bear all and any consequences of their acts. YOUR USE OF MATCHSPOT IS AT YOUR OWN RISK. THE USER IS SOLELY RESPONSIBLE FOR ANY LOSS OR DAMAGE ARISING OUT OF THAT USE. MATCHSPOT IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\" AND \"AS AVAILABLE\". TO THE EXTENT ALLOWED BY LAW, INC EXPRESSLY DISCLAIMS ALL RESPONSIBILITIES, WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. INC. DOES NOT REVIEW, MONITOR, AND OR CONTROL THE MESSAGES AND CONTENT OF USERS EVENTUALLY POSTED OR DISTRIBUTED IN THE MATCHSPOT, EVEN THROUGH ANY CHAT ROOMS, ELECTRONIC BULLETINS OR OTHER COMMUNICATION FORMS, AND WILL NOT BE IN ANY WAY RESPONSIBLE FOR SUCH MESSAGES. INC. INCLUDES, RESERVES THE RIGHT TO REMOVE, ON ITS SOLE DISCRETION, FOR ANY REASON AND WITHOUT NOTICE, ANY MESSAGES FROM USERS AND / OR MATCHSPOT CONTENT. INC IS NOT RESPONSIBLE FOR THE CONTENT, ADVERTISING AND INFORMATION AVAILABLE FROM AND / OR ARRANGED BY THIRD PARTIES ON THE MATCHSPOT, AS WELL AS FOR THE COMMUNICATIONS SET FORTH BY THE USERS WITH THE THIRD PARTIES, WHICH ARE THE ONLY RESPONSIBLE FOR THE INFORMATION AVAILABLE AND / OR